title: Storm Center Update - Saturday AM
text:
Storm Center Update - Saturday AM October 10, 2015, 4:49 AM by Grant Smith 
Summer returns to KELOLAND today. Highs this afternoon will climb into the 80s for most of the area. Upper level high pressure will keep skies clear today as well. 
Overnight lows in the low to middle 50s tonight with clear skies. 
Sunday will be a repeat of today with the sunshine and clear skies and 80s for highs. However, cooler air will start to descend in the Midwest; bringing temperatures back down to the 60s and 70s for next week but the biggest change tomorrow will be the winds. Sunday afternoon, the sustained winds will speed up to the 20s and 30s with gusts in the 30s and 40s. 
Next week is expected to be dry and sunny with highs in the 60s and 70s with lows in the 40s.
